Introduction
Over the past decade, the appearance of novel airborne
viruses and the reemergence of tuberculosis have posed
major public health threats. The most appropriate means
of protection, for health care workers (HCW) against such
threats, is not well defined.
Some studies have sug-
gested the use of surgical masks for HCWas inhalational
barrier protection.
